description: Number of covers of an unlabeled n-set such that every point of the set is covered by exactly 6 subsets of the cover and that intersection of every 6 subsets of the cover contains at most one point.
comments: Cover may include multiple occurrences of a subset. Also n-rowed binary matrices with distinct rows and all row sums 6.
author: _Vladeta Jovovic_, Nov 30 2000
